    "rationale": "The marker-free catchment view shows the most stretched coverage in the far northeast. Ground-truth distances confirm precinct 79 at (9.54, 9.70) is the worst-served current precinct, with nearest opened site distance 2.91 km to site 35 at (9.35, 6.80), and precinct 37 at (8.92, 8.90) is also long at 2.06 km to site 17. Closed site 16 at (8.51, 8.98) sits directly in that underserved pocket and would cut those distances sharply, while closing currently open site 35 at (9.35, 6.80) preserves the 18-site budget with limited expected harm because nearby open sites 17 at (7.45,7.45) and 31 at (8.78,4.22) still cover the mid-east. This targets the maximum nearest-open distance without broadly worsening central or southern precincts."
